  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Extensive mesh refinement studies, turbulence model benchmarking against published PIV data, and multi-operator repeatability checks collectively support a Medium assurance finding. The discretization error factor was subject to a rigorous Richardson extrapolation campaign across three systematically refined grids, and the resulting GCI values are well within the 5% threshold established for this COU. Validation against the FDA benchmark dataset yielded normalized RMS errors below 8% for all five flow-speed operating points, comfortably satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The assessment team is satisfied that the body of evidence is coherent and sufficient.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-cou1-hemolysis-worst-case",
